g the same KV cache shape, and implements a sigmoid Mo", "title": "Release v5.7.0", "topics": ["topic_release"], "updated_at": null}
{"artifact_links": ["https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/releases/tag/v0.20.0"], "author_or_org": "vllm-project", "canonical_url": "https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/releases/tag/v0.20.0", "collection_method": "github_releases", "confidence": "high", "content_hash": "711fb15bc9a0f583", "dedup_key": "github-release:vllm-project/vllm:v0.20.0", "event_id": "event_7ffe6fe2c09d6347", "evidence_type": "supported_fact", "excerpt": "# vLLM v0.20.0\r\n\r\n## Highlights\r\nThis release features 752 commits from 320 contributors (123 new)!\r\n\r\n* **DeepSeek V4**: Initial DeepSeek V4 support landed (#40860), with DSML token-leakage fix in DSV4/3.2 (#40806), DSA + MTP IMA fix (#40772), and a silu clamp limit on the shared expert (#40950).\r\n* **CUDA 13.0 default**: Default CUDA wheel on PyPI and `vllm/vllm-openai:v0.20.0` image switched to CUDA 13.0; architecture lists and build-args cleaned up (#39878), and CUDA bumped to 13.0.2 to matc", "identifiers": {"repo": "vllm-project/vllm", "tag": "v0.20.0"}, "inferred_entities": [], "item_type": "github_release", "novelty_score": 0.0, "published_at": "2026-04-27T21:20:28Z", "ranking_explanation": "", "raw_metadata": {"draft": "False", "prerelease": "False"}, "relevance_score": 0.0, "retrieved_at": "2026-04-30T11:53:01Z", "source_id": "gh-vllm", "source_name": "vLLM Releases", "source_native_id": "312943348", "source_policy": "public_official", "source_type": "implementation_source", "summary_hint": "# vLLM v0.20.0\r\n\r\n## Highlights\r\nThis release features 752 commits from 320 contributors (123 new)!\r\n\r\n* **DeepSeek V4**: Initial DeepSeek V4 support landed (#40860), with DSML token-leakage fix in DSV4/3.2 (#40806), DSA + MTP IMA fix (#40772), and a silu clamp limit on the shared expert (#40950).\r\n* **CUDA 13.0 default**: Default CUDA wheel on PyPI and `vllm/vllm-openai:v0.20.0` image switched to CUDA 13.0; architecture lists and build-args cleaned up (#39878), and CUDA bumped to 13.0.2 to matc", "title": "v0.20.0", "topics": ["topic_general"], "updated_at": null}
